text: we're a software-as-a-service vendor
that provides data management services
to government to help them track the
performance of their policies around the
world one of the biggest charges for us
as a small player as a small early-stage
startup is finding the right
infrastructure for us we're currently
working with a number of government
agencies in New South Wales one of the
biggest challenges was providing them
with onshore Australian based hosting
and fortunately we were able to get that
through AWS they were able to provide us
with the necessary infrastructure to
bring all of our services from our
original cloud platform in the US and
bring it all here to Australia the one
big benefit for us working with AWS has
been around how we're more prepared to
take our work globally we're a small
team that needs to be quite agile and
quite flexible in what we do and AWS has
given us the capability to meet those
needs we don't need to bring on a large
DevOps team when we've got the ability
to deploy it out to AWS products such as
SES and Fargate it allows us to do more
with less and provide those same
benefits off to our clients what I'm
most excited about with AWS is
continuing our work in the health and
social welfare spaces so that we can
continue to work with our government
clients to make sure that they can
manage and improve the lives of the
citizens that they work with thanks to
AWS we're being provided with the
infrastructure to work here locally in
Australia and be able to export our
technology on a global scale to compete
in in the international market
